{{Short description|Park in Nerima, Tokyo, Japan}}
{{Infobox park
| name = Musashiseki Park
| photo =  武蔵関公園「富士見池」（中之橋から北東ボート乗り場方面）練馬区.jpg
| photo_width = 250
| photo_caption = The park in 2006
| type = 

| location = [[Nerima|Nerima Ward]], [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]
| publictransit = [[Higashi-Fushimi Station]]
| coords = {{coord|35.727656|N|139.567809|E|type:landmark_region:JP||display=inline,title}}
| area = {{convert|45,985|m2|acre}}
| created = October 1938}}

{{nihongo|'''Musashiseki Park'''|武蔵関公園|Musashiseki Kōen}} is a public park in [[Nerima|Nerima Ward]], [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]].

==Overview==
Fujimi Pond is located in the park, and like the ponds in [[Shakujii Park]], [[Inokashira Park]], and Zenpukuji Park, this pond is formed by spring water from the [[Musashino Terrace]]. It is possible to go boating on the pond. The park is also a famous spot for cherry blossoms.

It opened as a private park in the [[Taishō era]], and since then, playground equipment and other facilities have been added.

==Access==
* By train: 5 minutes’ walk from [[Higashi-Fushimi Station]] on the [[File:Seibu shinjuku logo.svg|18px|E]] [[Seibu Shinjuku Line]]

==See also==
* [[Parks and gardens in Tokyo]]
* [[List of national parks of Japan|National Parks of Japan]]

==References==
{{Reflist}}
* [https://www.city.nerima.tokyo.jp/kankomoyoshi/annai/fukei/park/musashi/index.html Website of Nerima City (in Japanese)]

==External links==
* [https://1000enpark.com/park/00236/ Website of Let’s Go to the Park with 1,000 Yen! (in Japanese)]

{{Nerima}}


